title: Grateful Dead Live at Oakland-Alameda County Coliseum on 1979-02-17
description:
Set 1

Greatest Story Ever Told, Don't Ease Me In, Mama Tried, Mexicali Blues, Friend Of The Devil, Passenger, High Time, Looks Like Rain, Jack A Roe, Lazy Lightning-> Supplication

Set 2

Might As Well, I Need A Miracle-> Bertha-> Good Lovin', From The Heart Of Me, Big Railroad Blues, Terrapin Station-> Playin' In The Band-> Drums-> The Wheel-> Shakedown Street-> Playin' In The Band-> Sugar Magnolia, E: One More Saturday Night

Keith and Donna's Last showRock for Life Benefit to end environmental Cancer

reviews.review_text: Another great matrix job You and Hunter (plus others) deserve a lot of credit for keeping this place fresh.  Thanks!

This is definitely better in parts I streamed the audience for a while, but wanted it to sound like this.  Oops, I'm now in Terrapin and it sounds like sources aren't lining up. Switched back to the aud - Terrapin sounded better -  felt satisfied up to Shakedown.  Have now come back and Shakedown is better here.  Well, well, well.
- Goes back-and-forth from sloppy to pretty hot.
